THANKS!

As a Bamboo plan administrator I would like be able to define a plan level variable (e.g. MYJIRAVERSION) and then in the plan configuration (across all its stages and jobs) consistently refer to it, e.g. in builder definition:
{{mvn package -Djira.version=$MYJIRAVERSION}}

The reason: we need to maintain several parallel plans which compile and test the plugin against various JIRA versions. I think that such approach would be the most elegant - I could maintain just a single plan definition and then easily clone it to cope with different JIRA versions by just defining this single variable.
